Introduced Version
HOUSE BILL No. 1138
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 6-3-3-11.
Synopsis: Child care tax credit. Provides a child and dependent care
refundable tax credit against an individual's Indiana adjusted gross
income tax for employment related child and dependent care expenses
based on the taxpayer's Indiana adjusted gross income and a percentage
of the federal child and dependent care tax credit the taxpayer claimed
for the taxable year for federal income tax purposes.
Effective: January 1, 2026 (retroactive).
Hamilton
January 5, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Ways and Means.
